de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util

Class PartialExpressionTreeWalker

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util.ExpressionTreeWalker
      • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.evaluableexpressions.util.PartialExpressionTreeWalker
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ModifyingEvaluableExpressionVisitor, RecursiveEvaluableExpressionVisitor

    public abstract class PartialExpressionTreeWalker
extends ExpressionTreeWalker
    An evaluable expression tree walker allowing to ignore certain subtrees. The class offers a mechanism to stop visiting of inner expressions, forcing the visitor not to traverse the expression tree any further. Instead, the traversal will go “up” again, only calling after hooks, until it terminates at the root or traversal of inner expressions is activated again.

    • Method Detail

      • stopTraversingInnerExpressions

        protected void stopTraversingInnerExpressions()
        Stops visiting of inner expressions. As soon as this method is called, this visitor will no longer visit inner expressions. This means that only after hooks of already visited expressions will be called until the root is reached.
        See Also:
        startTraversingInnerExpressions()

      • startTraversingInnerExpressions

        protected void startTraversingInnerExpressions()
        Starts visiting of inner expressions. Inner expressions will be traverse depth-first as long as it is activated.
        See Also:
        stopTraversingInnerExpressions()

      • willTraverseInnerExpressions

        protected boolean willTraverseInnerExpressions()
        Queries whether the visitor will visit inner expressions. Will return true if startTraversingInnerExpressions() was called and false if stopTraversingInnerExpressions() was called.
        Returns:
        Whether inner expressions will be examined for the momentary tree.
